my-claw/sdp/prd-cypherclaw-sampler.md:1:# PRD: CypherClaw Sampler — Granular Memory Voice as Primary Instrument
my-claw/sdp/prd-cypherclaw-sampler.md:5:CypherClaw's signature palette is a quartet: `sw_bell_warm`, `sw_bowed`, `sw_breath`, `sw_pad`. These are synthesis voices — every sound they make is generated from oscillators, filters, and envelopes. They have no memory of the room, no memory of yesterday, no memory of what just happened. Every piece is born from silence.
my-claw/sdp/prd-cypherclaw-sampler.md:7:This PRD adds a fifth signature voice — **`sw_sampler`** — that elevates the room itself, the artist's recorded history, and a curated found-sound library into a primary instrument. The sampler is **how CypherClaw metabolizes the room**: it listens continuously to the contact mic and room mic, captures fragments worth remembering, and replays those fragments granularly — stretched, transposed, scrubbed, with a dedicated effects bus — back into the live performance.
my-claw/sdp/prd-cypherclaw-sampler.md:9:Three usages define the artistic intent:
my-claw/sdp/prd-cypherclaw-sampler.md:11:1. **Memory of place.** A continuous rolling buffer of contact + room input. When something is acoustically interesting (a transient cluster, a novel spectral signature, a sustained drone the room produces on its own), the buffer is captured to disk, tagged with the arc phase / mood / time / who-is-in-room, and made available to future scenes. Days later, those moments return — never literally, always granularly transformed — as quiet textures. The room composes itself through CypherClaw.
my-claw/sdp/prd-cypherclaw-sampler.md:19:1. **Granular by default, never one-shot.** The sampler is a granular voice with grain size 20–200 ms, density, position scrub, and pitch transpose. "Press button hear sample" is not a use case. Every play is a re-rendering through grains.
my-claw/sdp/prd-cypherclaw-sampler.md:22:4. **Self-listening as composition.** The composer's own past output is a primary source. CypherClaw learns from itself.
my-claw/sdp/prd-cypherclaw-sampler.md:23:5. **Restraint earned, not eroded.** The sampler joins the quartet to make a quintet, but it does not relax the 3-voice base / 2-voice deliberate / 4-voice climax discipline. Heavy sampler use replaces, not adds. In *Solitary* mode the sampler may be the *only* voice.
my-claw/sdp/prd-cypherclaw-sampler.md:29:**In scope:** a granular SuperCollider voice (`sw_sampler`) with a dedicated effects bus; a sample library on disk with tag-based selection; a continuous live-capture daemon for contact/room mics; a self-quotation loop; integration with the existing artist-mode selector and cast planner so the sampler joins the signature quintet; metrics and anti-pattern detection for sampler over- or under-use.
my-claw/sdp/prd-cypherclaw-sampler.md:33:- Full DAW-style multi-track sampler with chopping, slicing, or loop-point editing UI. The sampler is a granular voice, not a workstation.
my-claw/sdp/prd-cypherclaw-sampler.md:35:- Replacement of any existing signature voice. The quartet stays; the sampler is added to make a quintet.
my-claw/sdp/prd-cypherclaw-sampler.md:42:**Phase 1 — Foundations (CCS-001..CCS-008).** Sample data model, on-disk library layout, tag taxonomy, mood/mode-aware selector, character-registry entry for `voice_sampler`, signature-voice quintet update. Pure Python + tests. At end of phase, the selector picks plausible samples for any (mode, arc, mood) tuple from a library of stub/placeholder files; no audio plays yet.
my-claw/sdp/prd-cypherclaw-sampler.md:44:**Phase 2 — SuperCollider granular voice (CCS-009..CCS-014).** `sw_sampler.scd` SynthDef with grain-controlled buffer playback; buffer-management protocol for loading samples on demand; dedicated effects bus (delay + reverb + spectral freeze + comb-to-B); mix-engine integration so the sampler routes through the master bus. End of phase: sending OSC `/s_new sw_sampler bufnum=N grain_size=80ms density=12 pitch=0` plays a granular cloud audible through the speakers.
my-claw/sdp/prd-cypherclaw-sampler.md:48:**Phase 4 — Composer integration (CCS-022..CCS-028).** Mode-driven sampler density (solitary heavy, working light, etc.); `select_sample()` wired into cast/instrument-patch path so the composer treats the sampler as a first-class voice; self-quotation loop captures composer output when arc-payoff is high; keyboard/Theramini capture during human play; per-mode effects-bus presets; operator diagnostics surface currently-active samples. End of phase: pieces start to noticeably *cite themselves* across sessions, and the room's acoustic history becomes audible material.
my-claw/sdp/prd-cypherclaw-sampler.md:50:**Phase 5 — Verification + observability (CCS-029..CCS-033).** Per-piece sampler-event metrics; anti-pattern detection for sampler dominating (over-quote) or never appearing (silent quintet member); a sample-usage journal that records which samples played in which pieces with what transformations; end-to-end smoke test on cypherclaw confirming the daemon is capturing, the selector is choosing, the synth is playing, and the self-listener is observing the right output peaks. End of phase: composer can demonstrate a piece that uses 1 self-quotation + 1 room-capture + 1 library sample, all selector-chosen, all routed through the effects bus, all surfaced in the diagnostics dashboard.
my-claw/sdp/prd-cypherclaw-sampler.md:54:- `my-claw/sdp/prd-cypherclaw-humanization.md` — the rendering layer; sampler events flow through the same RenderPass (R-rules respect `role="sampler"` with grid_locked=False so phrasing applies, but R8 microtiming is dampened on grain-time-scale events).
my-claw/sdp/prd-cypherclaw-sampler.md:55:- `my-claw/tools/senseweave/artist_identity.py` — Mode-driven voice/tempo/density. `SIGNATURE_VOICES` extends from quartet to quintet; modes specify per-mode sampler density.
my-claw/sdp/prd-cypherclaw-sampler.md:56:- `my-claw/tools/senseweave/cast_planner.py` — `select_cast_ids` already supports `preferred_synths` and `voice_count_target`; the sampler joins the cast through this same path.
my-claw/sdp/prd-cypherclaw-sampler.md:57:- `my-claw/tools/senseweave/master_bus.py` and `mix_engine.py` — the sampler effects bus routes its summed output through the master, respecting amp/compression caps.
my-claw/sdp/prd-cypherclaw-sampler.md:58:- Existing `my-claw/tools/senseweave/synthesis/synthdefs/` directory and `boot_synthdefs.scd` — `sw_sampler.scsyndef` joins the boot-time SynthDef load.
my-claw/sdp/prd-cypherclaw-sampler.md:59:- Live JACK capture path — contact mic on `system:capture_FL` and room mic on `system:capture_FR` (Scarlett inputs already wired via `cypherclaw-jack.service`).
my-claw/sdp/prd-cypherclaw-sampler.md:64:- **New** `my-claw/tools/senseweave/synthesis/synthdefs/sw_sampler.scd` source + compiled `.scsyndef`
my-claw/sdp/prd-cypherclaw-sampler.md:65:- **New** `my-claw/tools/senseweave/synthesis/sampler_effects.scd` — dedicated effects bus SynthDef chain
my-claw/sdp/prd-cypherclaw-sampler.md:67:- **New** `my-claw/systemd/cypherclaw-sample-capture.service` — keeps the daemon alive across reboots
my-claw/sdp/prd-cypherclaw-sampler.md:70:- **New** `my-claw/tests/test_sampler_integration.py` — end-to-end composer → selector → OSC dispatch
my-claw/sdp/prd-cypherclaw-sampler.md:71:- **Extended** `my-claw/tools/senseweave/artist_identity.py` — `SIGNATURE_VOICES = (..., "sw_sampler")`; per-mode `sampler_density` field
my-claw/sdp/prd-cypherclaw-sampler.md:72:- **Extended** `my-claw/tools/senseweave/character_registry.py` — `voice_sampler` character with sampler-specific voice metadata
my-claw/sdp/prd-cypherclaw-sampler.md:73:- **Extended** `my-claw/tools/senseweave/instrument_patches.py` — patches reference sampler effects-bus presets
my-claw/sdp/prd-cypherclaw-sampler.md:74:- **Extended** `my-claw/tools/senseweave/master_bus.py` — sampler-bus mix slot with appropriate gain staging
my-claw/sdp/prd-cypherclaw-sampler.md:75:- **Extended** `my-claw/tools/duet_composer.py` — composer post-piece self-quotation hook + sampler dispatch path
my-claw/sdp/prd-cypherclaw-sampler.md:76:- **New** `samples/` directory layout under `/home/user/cypherclaw-data/samples/`:
my-claw/sdp/prd-cypherclaw-sampler.md:92:| CCS-004 | Define on-disk directory layout under `/home/user/cypherclaw-data/samples/` with `library/`, `self/`, `room/`, `contact/`, `theramini/`, `keyboard/` subdirs and `index.sqlite`. | MUST | T1 | - `SampleLibrary.bootstrap(root)` creates the six subdirectories + `index.sqlite` if missing, idempotent<br/>- documented as the canonical layout in module docstring<br/>- tests verify bootstrap on tmp dir creates all six subdirs and the SQLite file |
my-claw/sdp/prd-cypherclaw-sampler.md:94:| CCS-006 | Add `sw_sampler` to `SIGNATURE_VOICES` quintet in `artist_identity.py` and update `VOICE_ROLES` so a `"sampler"` role maps to `"sw_sampler"`. | MUST | T1 | - `SIGNATURE_VOICES` becomes `("sw_bell_warm", "sw_bowed", "sw_breath", "sw_pad", "sw_sampler")`<br/>- `VOICE_ROLES["sampler"] = "sw_sampler"`<br/>- existing `VOICE_ROLES` keys for melody/counter/color/texture/bass unchanged<br/>- existing `test_artist_identity.py::TestSignatureVoices::test_quartet_size` is renamed to `test_quintet_size` and asserts length 5; quartet-specific assertions migrated |
my-claw/sdp/prd-cypherclaw-sampler.md:95:| CCS-007 | Add `sampler_density` field (0.0–1.0) to `ArtistMode` with mode-specific values: solitary 0.7, companion 0.25, working_ambience 0.10, evening_reflection 0.65, storm 0.45. | MUST | T1 | - `ArtistMode` dataclass gains `sampler_density: float = 0.25` with documentation<br/>- existing five modes updated to the values above<br/>- `apply_mode_to_commission` propagates `sampler_density` into `mode_sampler_density` metadata<br/>- tests verify each mode's value, propagation, and that `sampler_density` is bounded [0.0, 1.0] |
my-claw/sdp/prd-cypherclaw-sampler.md:96:| CCS-008 | Register `voice_sampler` character in `character_registry.py` with `voice.synth = "sw_sampler"`, `voice.role = "sampler"`, default register, and per-mode gain overrides. | MUST | T1 | - `character_registry.py` gains `voice_sampler` entry with synth=`sw_sampler`, role=`sampler`, register=`[36, 84]`, params containing default grain_size_ms, density, pitch_transpose<br/>- character is selectable by `select_cast_ids` when `preferred_synths` includes `sw_sampler`<br/>- tests verify registration and selection through cast planner |
my-claw/sdp/prd-cypherclaw-sampler.md:97:| CCS-009 | Implement `sw_sampler.scd` granular SynthDef with bufnum, grain-size, density, position-scrub, pitch-transpose, attack/release envelope, and effects-bus send. | MUST | T1 | - SynthDef args: `bufnum`, `amp` (default 0.5), `grain_size_ms` (default 80, range 20–200), `density` (default 12 grains/sec), `position` (0..1 normalized), `position_rate` (scrub speed), `pitch_transpose_semitones` (default 0), `pitch_jitter_semitones` (default 0.1), `attack_sec` (default 0.05), `release_sec` (default 0.2), `gate` (default 1, sustained), `out_bus` (default 0), `fx_send` (default 0.4)<br/>- `doneAction:2` self-frees on envelope end<br/>- compiled `sw_sampler.scsyndef` lives in `synthesis/synthdefs/`<br/>- SC-side test (`my-claw/supercollider/test_sw_sampler.scd`) renders 2-second clip from a known buffer and verifies non-silence + spectral characteristics<br/>- gate=0 triggers release tail correctly |
my-claw/sdp/prd-cypherclaw-sampler.md:98:| CCS-010 | Implement buffer-management protocol: `OnSamplerLoad(record)` allocates scsynth buffer + reads WAV; `OnSamplerFree` releases buffer; LRU eviction at 64-buffer cap. | MUST | T1 | - `tools/senseweave/sampler_buffers.py` exposes `BufferPool(scsynth_client, capacity=64)` with `acquire(record) -> bufnum`, `release(record)`, `evict_lru()`<br/>- WAV file path → `/b_allocRead bufnum path 0 -1` over OSC<br/>- LRU eviction triggered automatically when `acquire` exceeds capacity<br/>- on scsynth restart, pool detects buffer-id reuse failure and rebuilds<br/>- tests with a mock OSC client verify allocate, evict, release, and reuse paths |
my-claw/sdp/prd-cypherclaw-sampler.md:99:| CCS-011 | Implement `sampler_effects.scd` dedicated effects-bus SynthDef chain: long delay (1/4 to 1/2 measure), convolution reverb (FreeVerb fallback if no IR loaded), spectral freeze (PV_Freeze), comb-resonance tuned to B fundamental (61.74 Hz). | MUST | T1 | - SynthDef `sw_sampler_fx` reads from a stereo bus and writes to master bus<br/>- args: `delay_time` (sec, default 0.5), `delay_feedback` (0..0.85, default 0.55), `verb_mix` (default 0.35), `room_size` (default 0.7), `freeze_amount` (0..1, default 0.0), `comb_b_amount` (0..1, default 0.25), `comb_b_freq` (default 61.74)<br/>- bus number conventionally 16 (stereo, so 16+17)<br/>- compiled `sw_sampler_fx.scsyndef` lives in `synthesis/synthdefs/`<br/>- SC-side test verifies non-silent output for a known impulse input and frequency-domain check that 61.74 Hz comb peak is present when `comb_b_amount > 0` |
my-claw/sdp/prd-cypherclaw-sampler.md:100:| CCS-012 | Implement `sampler_dispatch.py` that converts a `(SampleRecord, PerformanceIntent, params)` tuple into the OSC bundle (`/s_new sw_sampler ...` + buffer-pool acquire) and ships it to scsynth. | MUST | T1 | - `dispatch_sample(record, intent, *, position, position_rate, grain_size_ms, density, pitch_transpose, amp, fx_send) -> SamplerHandle` issues `/b_allocRead` (if needed), `/s_new sw_sampler ...` and returns a handle for later `/n_set gate 0` release<br/>- correlates `record.gain_db` with `amp`<br/>- handles per-mode effects presets (delay_time / verb_mix / freeze / comb_b vary by mode)<br/>- tests with mock OSC client verify correct bundle ordering, gate-release path, and per-mode preset application |
my-claw/sdp/prd-cypherclaw-sampler.md:101:| CCS-013 | Per-voice gate-controlled lifecycle: composer can `play_sampler(record, duration_sec)` for fire-and-forget OR `start_sampler(record) -> handle; stop_sampler(handle)` for sustained voices. | MUST | T1 | - `sampler_dispatch.play_sampler(record, duration_sec, **params)` schedules a fire-and-forget grain cloud with an internal envelope of `duration_sec`<br/>- `start_sampler` / `stop_sampler` returns/uses a handle for sustained sampler voices that match the bowed/pad lifecycle<br/>- both code paths feed through the same `dispatch_sample` core<br/>- tests verify both lifecycles and that they can run concurrently without buffer-id collision |
my-claw/sdp/prd-cypherclaw-sampler.md:102:| CCS-014 | Integrate sampler effects bus into `master_bus.py` mix slot with appropriate gain staging (peak-normalized, not RMS) and post-mix compression bypass to preserve grain transients. | MUST | T1 | - `master_bus.apply_master_bus_scene` recognizes a `sampler_bus` mix slot with default gain -3 dB (peak-normalized so quieter library samples don't disappear)<br/>- post-mix compression for the sampler slot has `compression_ratio = 1.5` (lower than the 4.0 used elsewhere) so grain transients survive<br/>- tests verify gain staging on a known-amplitude input and grain-transient preservation via peak-vs-RMS ratio |
my-claw/sdp/prd-cypherclaw-sampler.md:103:| CCS-015 | Implement `sample_capture_daemon.py` rolling 60-second buffers reading from `system:capture_1` (contact mic) and `system:capture_2` (room mic) via JACK. | MUST | T1 | - daemon opens two JACK ports `cypherclaw-capture:in_contact` and `cypherclaw-capture:in_room`<br/>- each maintains a 60-second numpy ring buffer at 48 kHz<br/>- exposes `get_window(source, duration_sec, offset_sec) -> np.ndarray` for the moment-detector to pull recent windows<br/>- handles JACK xruns gracefully (logs, does not crash)<br/>- tests with a synthetic JACK input fixture verify ring-buffer correctness, window extraction, and xrun recovery |
my-claw/sdp/prd-cypherclaw-sampler.md:108:| CCS-020 | Add systemd unit `cypherclaw-sample-capture.service` that runs `sample_capture_daemon.py` with `Restart=always`, dependent on `cypherclaw-jack.service`. | MUST | T2 | - unit file at `my-claw/systemd/cypherclaw-sample-capture.service`<br/>- `User=user`, `LimitMEMLOCK=infinity`, `ExecStart=/home/user/cypherclaw/.venv/bin/python3 /home/user/cypherclaw/tools/sample_capture_daemon.py`<br/>- `After=cypherclaw-jack.service`, `Requires=cypherclaw-jack.service`<br/>- enabled on boot via `cypherclaw_boot.sh`<br/>- daemon survives a 30-minute soak test with simulated JACK xruns |
my-claw/sdp/prd-cypherclaw-sampler.md:110:| CCS-022 | Wire `SampleSelector` into `cast_planner.select_cast_ids` so when the cast includes `sw_sampler`, a sample is pre-selected for the piece and attached to the cast metadata. | MUST | T1 | - `select_cast_ids` (or a sibling `assemble_cast`) returns cast entries with optional `sample_record: SampleRecord` field for sampler voices<br/>- selection happens once per piece commission and passes mode + arc_phase + mood + target_character (drawn from `instrument_patches.select_instrument_patch`)<br/>- tests verify sampler voices in cast carry a sample_record and that the record matches selector contracts |
my-claw/sdp/prd-cypherclaw-sampler.md:111:| CCS-023 | Per-mode sampler density gates: composer plays `floor(sampler_density * total_phrases) + Bernoulli(sampler_density)` sampler events per piece (clamped 0..total). | MUST | T1 | - `tools/duet_composer.py` reads `mode_sampler_density` and schedules sampler events accordingly within the song's tracker timeline<br/>- evening_reflection at 0.65 produces noticeably more sampler events than working_ambience at 0.10 in 100-piece simulated runs<br/>- never schedules more sampler events than total phrases in the piece<br/>- tests verify density-to-count math, clamp behavior, and per-mode separation |
my-claw/sdp/prd-cypherclaw-sampler.md:113:| CCS-025 | Sample-aware harmonic planning: when a sample with known `pitch_hz` is selected, transpose to fit the current piece's key by computing the closest in-key root and applying `pitch_transpose_semitones`. | MUST | T1 | - `sampler_dispatch::transpose_to_key(record, key_name) -> semitones` returns the integer transposition that maps `record.pitch_hz` to the nearest pitch in the current key (B-rooted modes preferred)<br/>- when `record.pitch_confidence < 0.4`, transposition is set to 0 and the sample plays "atonally" as a texture<br/>- tests verify transposition for known pitch + key combinations, low-confidence pass-through, and edge cases (octave wraps) |
my-claw/sdp/prd-cypherclaw-sampler.md:114:| CCS-026 | Add per-mode effects-bus presets: solitary/evening favor more reverb + delay; working_ambience uses minimal effects; storm uses high freeze + heavy comb-B. | MUST | T1 | - `sampler_dispatch::FX_PRESETS_BY_MODE: dict[str, dict]` mapping mode name to fx args<br/>- solitary: `delay_time=0.6, delay_feedback=0.65, verb_mix=0.45, freeze_amount=0.2, comb_b_amount=0.4`<br/>- companion: `delay_time=0.5, delay_feedback=0.4, verb_mix=0.3, freeze_amount=0.0, comb_b_amount=0.15`<br/>- working_ambience: `delay_time=0.3, delay_feedback=0.2, verb_mix=0.15, freeze_amount=0.0, comb_b_amount=0.1`<br/>- evening_reflection: `delay_time=0.7, delay_feedback=0.55, verb_mix=0.5, freeze_amount=0.15, comb_b_amount=0.3`<br/>- storm: `delay_time=0.25, delay_feedback=0.7, verb_mix=0.25, freeze_amount=0.55, comb_b_amount=0.6`<br/>- tests verify each preset, that values are within SynthDef-acceptable ranges, and that `dispatch_sample` correctly applies the preset for the active mode |
my-claw/sdp/prd-cypherclaw-sampler.md:115:| CCS-027 | Surface "currently sampling X" + "playing sample Y from source Z" in `operator_diagnostics.py` and the face/inkplate display. | MUST | T2 | - `operator_diagnostics.py::sampler_status() -> dict` returns `{capture_active: bool, capture_seconds_buffered: int, last_capture: dict, current_playback: list[dict]}`<br/>- daemon writes `/tmp/sampler_state.json` every 1 sec for the diagnostic to read<br/>- face/inkplate renderers gain a one-line "♫ sampling room" / "♫ memory: <self/2026-04-25>" banner<br/>- tests verify state-file schema and diagnostic output format |
my-claw/sdp/prd-cypherclaw-sampler.md:117:| CCS-029 | Implement `metrics::sampler_event_count_per_piece` and `metrics::sampler_library_vs_self_ratio` for the metrics-CI gate. | MUST | T1 | - integrated with the existing render `metrics.py` (CCH-014)<br/>- per-piece event count is recorded and surfaced in operator diagnostics<br/>- library:self ratio is computed across the last 50 pieces; healthy band 1.5..3.0<br/>- tests verify metric computation and threshold reporting |
my-claw/sdp/prd-cypherclaw-sampler.md:118:| CCS-030 | Implement anti-pattern detectors: `sampler_dominating` (sampler event count > 0.6 × total events) and `sampler_silent_quintet_member` (sampler used in <5% of last 50 pieces, mode-weighted). | MUST | T1 | - integrated into `render/antipatterns.py` (CCH-015)<br/>- `sampler_dominating` fires per-piece, surfaces in metrics gate as warning (downgrade to MUST FIX after 3 consecutive)<br/>- `sampler_silent_quintet_member` fires across rolling window of last 50 pieces; mode-weighted means the threshold scales with `sampler_density` per mode (so working_ambience never trips it)<br/>- tests verify each detector with synthetic piece histories |
my-claw/sdp/prd-cypherclaw-sampler.md:119:| CCS-031 | End-to-end smoke test on cypherclaw: capture a known room sound, watch the composer self-quote it within 3 pieces, verify the self-listener observes the resulting peaks. | MUST | T1 | - `my-claw/tests/test_sampler_e2e.py` (skipped on CI, runs on cypherclaw via `pytest -m cypherclaw_e2e`)<br/>- plays a 4-second sine sweep through the speakers, lets contact/room mic capture it, waits for the daemon to detect+tag, forces the composer to compose 3 short pieces, asserts at least one of them dispatched a sampler with the captured sample<br/>- self-listener observes nonzero peak in the expected scene<br/>- documented in `docs/sampler-smoke-test.md` |
my-claw/sdp/prd-cypherclaw-sampler.md:121:| CCS-033 | Update `docs/cypherclaw-musicianship-roadmap.md` to reflect the quintet, document the sampler architecture in `docs/cypherclaw-sampler-architecture.md`, and add a one-page artistic-intent doc `docs/cypherclaw-sampler-artistic-intent.md`. | MUST | T2 | - musicianship roadmap mentions the quintet and sampler-as-memory<br/>- architecture doc covers the data model, daemon, dispatch, effects bus, and selector<br/>- artistic-intent doc captures the three usages (memory of place, self-quotation, found library) and the five principles<br/>- docs link from each other; mkdocs / repo nav updated if applicable |
my-claw/sdp/prd-cypherclaw-sampler.md:131:The piece's sample-usage journal entry shows all three samples, their transformations, and the arc-payoff. The face/inkplate display showed "♫ sampling room" during the piece, then "♫ memory: self/<song_id>" when the self-quotation played. The metrics-CI gate reports `sampler_event_count = 3`, `sampler_dominating = false`, and `sampler_silent_quintet_member = false`.
my-claw/sdp/prd-cypherclaw-sampler.md:133:The room is now an instrument. CypherClaw remembers itself.
