my-claw/tools/workspace/research_e994d8dd.md:15:The `promptclaw.json` for "CypherClaw" mentions an interface with "LifeImprover" and the "LDP process," so I'll investigate how these are technically represented. I'll check `docs/PROJECT_GUIDE.md` and other documentation to see if "LifeImprover" is a standard app or a custom tool.
my-claw/tools/workspace/research_e994d8dd.md:18:`tools/sdp_bridge.py` and `tools/cypherclaw_daemon.py` are likely key to understanding the integration. I'll examine `sdp_bridge.py` and check for any relationship between "SDP" (Self/Success Design Protocol), "LDP" (Life Design Protocol), and "sdp-cli".
my-claw/tools/workspace/research_e994d8dd.md:19:`sdp_bridge.py` links to `sdp-cli`, a pipeline engine where "SDP" (likely Success Design Protocol) serves as the execution layer for the higher-level "LDP" (Life Design Protocol). I'll now examine `tools/cypherclaw_daemon.py` to understand their interaction.
my-claw/tools/workspace/research_e994d8dd.md:20:I'm searching `cypherclaw_daemon.py` for "LifeImprover" or "LDP".
my-claw/tools/workspace/research_e994d8dd.md:21:"LifeImprover" is Anthony's Django-based life-tracking app, while "sdp-cli" is his "Success Design Protocol" pipeline engine. "LDP" (Life Design Protocol) is the framework "PromptClaw" (CypherClaw) orchestrates, using "sdp-cli" for execution. I'll now investigate if "LifeImprover" has a REST/GraphQL API or if "LDP" uses a specific data format by searching for "LifeImprover" in the current project, specifically checking `tools/researcher.py` and `tools/observatory.py` for API calls or library imports.
