my-claw/sdp/prd-cypherclaw-humanization.md:1:# PRD: CypherClaw Humanization — Structured Expression Rendering Layer
my-claw/sdp/prd-cypherclaw-humanization.md:5:CypherClaw already composes legible music: score trees, section functions, production profiles, genre strategies, SenseWeave mappings. But the path from composed score to synthesized audio still renders too rigidly. Phrases don't breathe. Repeated motifs don't vary. Silence is a byproduct of scheduling rather than an intentional voice. Sensors occasionally read like one-to-one controllers rather than shaping aggregate intent. The result is the "almost-human" failure mode: structurally competent, expressively flat.
my-claw/sdp/prd-cypherclaw-humanization.md:17:5. **Machine identity preserved.** Grid-locked elements (ostinati, sequencers, polyrhythmic machines), superhuman precision, and alien timbres are deliberately *not* humanized. CypherClaw is a robot musician that has learned which things humans shape — not a robot pretending to be a violinist.
my-claw/sdp/prd-cypherclaw-humanization.md:19:The goal is not realism. It is **legibility**: a listener should feel that CypherClaw *intended* each phrase — to build, to withhold, to answer the room.
my-claw/sdp/prd-cypherclaw-humanization.md:27:- Photorealistic human-performance imitation. CypherClaw is a robot musician, not a violinist simulator.
my-claw/sdp/prd-cypherclaw-humanization.md:48:- `docs/cypherclaw-score-tree-composition-spec.md` — the score-tree composer this layer renders from.
my-claw/sdp/prd-cypherclaw-humanization.md:49:- `docs/cypherclaw-musicianship-roadmap.md` — reference for existing musicianship vocabulary.
